{
  "ComponentID": "IP2312",
  "ComponentType": "Single-Cell Li-ion/Li-Polymer Synchronous Buck Charger IC",
  "Description": "The IP2312 is a monolithic synchronous switching buck charger IC designed for single-cell lithium-ion/polymer batteries. It operates from a 5V input, integrates power MOSFETs, and uses a 750kHz switching frequency to achieve high efficiency (up to 94% at 3.7V/2A). It features programmable charging current via an external resistor, supports multiple battery termination voltages (4.2V/4.3V/4.35V/4.4V), and includes comprehensive protection such as input OVP/UVP, NTC temperature monitoring, charge timeout, and IC overtemperature protection. It requires minimal external components and is offered in an ESOP8 package.",
